.SH "struct pdg::SpriteAnimateEvent"
.PP 
a Sprite did some animation (\fIOptional\fP) 

A Sprite will generate one of these events when it completes an animation including fades (opacity animations), and moving on/offscreen or outside of the layer\&.

.PP
For frame based animations -- that is, calls to \fBpdg\&.Sprite\&.startFrameAnimation()\fP -- if it reaches the last frame and is not set to loop, action will be \fBpdg\&.action_AnimationEnd\fP\&. For looping animations \fBpdg\&.action_AnimationLoop\fP will be received each time the animation completes and starts over with the first frame\&.

.PP
When a Spriter animation blend -- started by \fBpdg\&.Sprite\&.blendToAnimation()\fP -- completes, action will be \fBpdg\&.action_AnimationBlendComplete\fP

.PP
For Spriter triggers embedded in a Spriter animation, action will be \fBpdg\&.action_SpriterTrigger\fP

.PP
For fades, one of three action types are possible: \fBpdg\&.action_FadeComplete\fP for calls to \fBpdg\&.Sprite\&.fadeTo()\fP, \fBpdg\&.action_FadeInComplete\fP for calls to \fBpdg\&.Sprite\&.fadeIn()\fP, and \fBpdg\&.action_FadeOutComplete\fP for calls to \fBpdg\&.Sprite\&.fadeOut()\fP\&.

.PP
When a Sprite has setWantsOffscreenEvents(true), \fBpdg\&.action_Offscreen\fP and \fBpdg\&.action_Onscreen\fP events will be generated for that sprite whenever it enters or departs the visible area of the port the layer is being rendered into\&.

.PP
When a Sprite has setWantsCollideWallEvents(true), \fBpdg\&.action_ExitLayer\fP events will be generated for that sprite whenever it moves completely outside the boundaries of the layer\&. (It will also get a \fBSpriteCollideEvent\fP when it hits the boundary)\&. 
.PP
.nf
{
    emitter: {},       // the emitter that generated this event
    eventType: 17,     // the event type (eventType_SpriteAnimate)
    action: 0,         // what happened (action_AnimationEnd/Loop or action_Fade/In/OutComplete)
    actingSprite: {},  // the Sprite that was animating
    inLayer: {}        // the SpriteLayer that contains the Sprite
}

.fi
.PP

.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
At this time other kinds of animations such as calls to \fBpdg::Sprite\&.startAnimation()\fP do not generate any events\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBpdg\&.eventType_SpriteAnimate\fP 

.PP
\fBpdg\&.Sprite\&.startFrameAnimation()\fP 

.PP
