.SS "const eventType_KeyDown = 4"

.PP
the user pushed down on a key Generated by the \fBEventManager\fP when the user first pushes down on a key\&. Use this for arcade style key handling\&.

.PP
To detect the key being released, use \fBeventType_KeyUp\fP\&. For keyboard data entry, use \fBeventType_KeyPress\fP\&.

.PP
\fBPlatform-Specific Key Codes\fP
.RS 4

.RE
.PP
The #KeyEvent\&.keyCode field contains \fBplatform-specific raw hardware keycodes\fP that vary by operating system (Mac uses NSEvent scan codes, Windows uses VK_* virtual key codes, Linux uses GLFW scan codes)\&.

.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
For cross-platform key detection, use \fBeventType_KeyPress\fP instead\&. However, since modifier keys (shift, control, alt/option, meta/command) don't generate KeyPress events, PDG provides platform-aware constants like \fBkeyCode_LeftShift\fP and \fBkeyCode_Control\fP that work correctly on all platforms\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
